
Overview of noun separation

The noun separation has 9 senses (first 5 from tagged texts)
                                     
1. (3) separation -- (the state of lacking unity)
2. (3) separation, breakup, detachment -- (coming apart)
3. (1) interval, separation -- (the distance between things; "fragile items require separation and cushioning")
4. (1) separation -- (sorting one thing from others; "the separation of wheat from chaff"; "the separation of mail by postal zones")
5. (1) separation -- (the social act of separating or parting company; "the separation of church and state")
6. separation -- (the space where a division or parting occurs; "he hid in the separation between walls")
7. separation -- (the termination of employment (by resignation or dismissal))
8. legal separation, separation -- ((law) the cessation of cohabitation of man and wife (either by mutual agreement or under a court order))
9. separation -- (the act of dividing or disconnecting)
